<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596043>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Habitus images of conifer-inhabiting Pilophorus spp. (A–C) and Pherolepis spp. (D–H), live adults and 5th instar nymph (G). A. Pilophorus miyamotoi ♂. B. P. validicornis ♀ (image courtesy of M. Nozawa). C. P. tagoi ♀ (courtesy of M. Nozawa). D. Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp., ♂. E. Same, lateral view. F. Same, ♀. G. Same, 5th instar nymph, ♂. H. Pherolepis fasciatus ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596043/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596041>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus images of Pilophorus spp., live adult individuals. A–B. P. satoyamanus n. sp. ♂ (images courtesy of M. Takai). C–D. P. okamotoi ♂. E. P. setulosellus n. sp. ♀ (courtesy of M. Takai). F. P. setulosus ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596041/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596075>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus okamotoi (with black circles●) and P. satoyamanus n. sp. A–B, I–J. Anterior body, left lateral view. C, K. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. D, N, O. Apex of pygophore, left lateral view. E. Apex of pygophore, with parameres and exposed endosoma. F–G. Endosoma. H, L–M. Metatarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596075/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596077>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus setulosellus n. sp. (with black circles●) and P. setulosus. A. Right dorsolateral habitus. B. Right lateral habitus. C, K. Ventral habitus. D. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. E, L. Pygophore, dorsal view. Scutellum. F, M. Endosoma. G, O. Metatarsus. H, N. Right paramere. I. Dorsal habitus. J. Left lateral habitus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596077/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596027>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Habitus images of Pilophorus spp. A. P. choii ♂. B. P. maeharai, holotype ♂. C. P. niger ♀. D–E. P. pullulus, holotype ♀ (Taiwan). F–G. P. pullulus ♂ (Amami-Oshima Is., Japan)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596027/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596029>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Habitus images of Pilophorus spp., live individuals. A. P. erraticus ♂. B. P. erraticus ♀. C–D. P. pseudoperplexus ♂. E. P. nakatanii, holotype ♂. F. P. lucidus ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596029/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596053>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Male genitalia of Pilophorus spp. A–E, I–K. P. hyotan n. sp. (from Nagasaki, Japan: A–C, K; Solkhumbu, Nepal: D–E, I–J). F–H, L–N. P. typicus (Nakhon Nayok, Thailand: F–G; India: H, L–M; Nagasaki: N). O. P. miyamotoi (Kochi Pref., Japan). P–S. P. pullulus (Amami-Oshima Is.). A– B, D, F–G, O–P. Endosoma (vesica). C, E, H, S. Phallotheca. I–N, Q–R. Parameres." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596053/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596071>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus hyotan n. sp. (with black circles●) and P. typicus. A. Left lateral habitus. B, K. Dorsal habitus. C, L. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. D, J. Ventral habitus. E, F, M. Scutellum. G, N, O. Apex of pygophore (with sensory lobe of left paramere), left lateral view. H–I, P–Q. Metatarsus. G. Same, pretarsal structure." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596071/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596073>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Scanning electron micrographs of male (A–J) and female (K–O) genitalia for Pilophorus hyotan n. sp. (with black circles●) and P. typicus. A, H. Pygophore, dorsal view. B. Left paramere. C. Right paramere. D, G. Same, with exposed endosoma (vesica). E–F, I–J. Endosoma. K–O. Posterior wall of bursae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596073/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

